{"abstract":[{"text":"Hashed string","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"title":"sdbmhash","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:SS11SwiftExtrasE8sdbmhashSivp","extendedModule":"Swift","modules":[{"relatedModules":["Swift"],"name":"SwiftExtras"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sdbmhash","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/String"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/String\/sdbmhash","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sdbmhash","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This algorithm was created for sdbm (a public-domain reimplementation of ndbm) database library.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it was found to do well in scrambling bits, causing better distribution of the keys and fewer splits.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it also happens to be a good general hashing function with good distribution.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the actual function is hash(i) = hash(i - 1) * 65599 + str[i];","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"what is included below is the faster version used in gawk.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[there is even a faster, duff-device version] the magic prime constant 65599 (2^6 + 2^16 - 1)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"was picked out of thin air while experimenting with many different constants.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this is one of the algorithms used in berkeley db (see sleepycat) and elsewhere.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/string\/sdbmhash"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","title":"Swift","kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"type":"topic","role":"collection"},"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift/String/sdbmhash":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sdbmhash","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"sdbmhash","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Hashed string"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/String\/sdbmhash","url":"\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/string\/sdbmhash","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift/String":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/String","url":"\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/string","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"String","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"String"},"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/